describe.a: I had to draw lines to make a ball roll into a cup. Sometimes there was wind or obstacles in the way.

approach.a: I generally drew a line so the ball rolled or bounced into the cup, but I also drew a line on the other side of the cup to make sure the ball didn't bounce out.

survey-comments.a: Sometimes it took the ball a little bit of time to stop rolling around if there was wind, because it kept blowing back and forth slightly. It'd be nice if the ball just stopped after a couple of seconds of not moving.
